language Essence 1.3

given n, k, numColours : int(1..)
given edges : set of set (size 2) of int(1..n)

find colouring : matrix indexed by [int(1..n)] of set (size k) of int(1..numColours)

such that
    forAll edge in edges .
        forAll u in edge . forAll v in edge . u < v ->
            |colouring[u] intersect colouring[v]| = 0,
    $ Symmetry breaking: fix the colour set of vertex 1
    colouring[1] = toSet([ i | i : int(1..k) ])
